{"ts":"2026-06-12T22:48:14.706Z","author":"audit-quality-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-oxq2"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Project-scope extension install writes ~69MB node_modules per workspace (peer pm-cli + transitive Sentry/OTel)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":".agents/pm/extensions/pm-changelog/node_modules is 69MB: @unbrained/pm-cli 25MB (installed because runtimeDependencyInstallSpecs in src/cli/commands/extension/install-sources.ts:454-456 deliberately includes peerDependencies so SDK imports resolve inside the extension dir) plus its transitive @sentry 22MB + @opentelemetry 21MB. Gitignored, so no repo bloat, but every workspace that runs pm install npm:pm-changelog (including the changelog:pm CI/release path on every changelog check) pays the download+disk cost, and the nested pm-cli copy can version-skew against the host. Ideas: symlink/inject the running CLI's own install root to satisfy the peer instead of reinstalling it; or publish a slim SDK-only package for extensions to peer on; or npm install --omit=peer plus an explicit resolution shim for @unbrained/pm-cli. Needs care: PR#74 learning says package extensions rely on the resolvable peer for defineExtension imports."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["audit-2026-06-13","disk","extensions","performance"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:48:14.706Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:48:14.706Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"audit-quality-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-y7sc"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"90aaba01962575d3cc3393c5b8f682dfeefa09746a4caf2383ac48dd4720602f","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-06-18T00:03:43.439Z","author":"codex-audit-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-18T00:03:43.439Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-18T00:03:43.439Z","author":"codex-audit-agent","text":"Audit evidence from PR #266 on 2026-06-18: pnpm changelog:pm regenerated CHANGELOG.md successfully, but the subsequent pnpm changelog:pm:check wrapper stalled for several minutes inside pm install npm:pm-changelog --project -> npm install @unbrained/pm-cli@>=2026.6.7. Direct installed-extension check via node dist/cli.js changelog generate --check returned unchanged. This confirms the project-scope extension peer install cost can block release/check workflows, not just consume disk."}]}],"before_hash":"90aaba01962575d3cc3393c5b8f682dfeefa09746a4caf2383ac48dd4720602f","after_hash":"2bc649286bfe409b1c01b38d60bab64b516868edfa6cde0526c24af55e94436b"}
